{"id": "1428214815586910219", "channel_id": "1326453691527594035", "type": 19, "author_id": "192510170935328769", "author_name": "rozu", "author_bot": false, "content": "You can try this Jenkins team out, replace castor with Alva since you dont have castor. Use Alva card to give Jenkins more cards for her ulti", "timestamp": "2025-10-16T02:55:46.984000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": ["518144435863683072"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [{"id": "1428214814882136156", "filename": "Screenshot_20251015_195205_Morimens.jpg", "content_type": "image/jpeg", "size": 154911, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1326453691527594035/1428214814882136156/Screenshot_20251015_195205_Morimens.jpg?ex=6a355872&is=6a3406f2&hm=224e11ffdb81c6d56257e0a12f9ba0248da2e45b7efdd45953a5264a1852186b&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1428063794881495072", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1428215085473730572", "channel_id": "1326453691527594035", "type": 0, "author_id": "192510170935328769", "author_name": "rozu", "author_bot": false, "content": "Faros is for secondary damage  so that if you lose Jenkins your wincon is still faros sniping, and corpo enables Jenkins and to some extent faros while also having burst damage of her own with ulti and her two cost.", "timestamp": "2025-10-16T02:56:51.330000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "❤️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1428258408967966753", "channel_id": "1326453691527594035", "type": 19, "author_id": "108392615644278784", "author_name": "alistiel", "author_bot": false, "content": "I think you should replace your wheels and try to find a more appropriate posse than Eternal Obsession or Undying Thunder. \n\nYou're basically going to be running into one of three teams early on; strike-based teams, poison-based teams, and anti-poison compositions using stuff like Nobleman's Staff and/or ~~whatever Celeste's wheel is called~~ Sail of Providence. If you don't have a plan for those teams, and don't have a very strong plan to kill everyone you meet early and often, you'll encounter problems when their plan takes off before yours. Winter's Requiem is kind of a good-stuff wheel, Punishment is the kind of thing you end up with when you expect to use your exalt more than a couple of times or if it's basically just... what your exalt already does... and Wheel Unseen is an expensive wheel that may not be the best choice for really anybody since all of their costs are low.", "timestamp": "2025-10-16T05:49:00.456000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-10-16T06:17:10.629000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": ["518144435863683072"], "reactions": [{"emoji": "❤️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1428063794881495072", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1428258830810087465", "channel_id": "1326453691527594035", "type": 19, "author_id": "108392615644278784", "author_name": "alistiel", "author_bot": false, "content": "If you're anticipating successfully reviving people constantly, then you can do funny shit like Death of Mrs. Coral, or dispose of your tank entirely and use a healthy strike based DPS like Caecus with ~~oh fuck that's *me* that's my 24 team~~ Will Unyielding (as a Fortress tank) or Fin of Sorrow (as a suicide brick you throw at the enemy and bring back)", "timestamp": "2025-10-16T05:50:41.031000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-10-16T06:18:46.128000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "❤️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1428064741749686353", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
